"Accessing applications in the <a href=\"http://gnome3.org/\">GNOME 3</a> "
"desktop environment."
msgstr "在 <a href=\"http://gnome3.org/\">GNOME 3</a> 桌面环境下选择应用程序。"

#. translators: This is the description of the "trisquel1.png" screenshot.
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:25
msgid "Update manager open."
msgstr "更新管理器"

#. translators: This is the description of the "trisquel2.png" screenshot.
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:27
msgid "LibreOffice Calc open, showing an example spreadsheet."
msgstr "LibreOffice Calc 中的一张电子表格。"

#. translators: This is the description of the "trisquel3.png" screenshot.
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:29
msgid "Accessing applications."
msgstr "访问应用程序。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:45
msgid ""
"Because there is no &quot;one Linux&quot;, finding what you need can be "
"difficult. Here are our choice of three beginner-friendly, widely used "
"distributions."
msgstr "由于没有一个“统一的 Linux”，找一款你需要的可能比较困难。这是我们挑选三个适合新手，使用广泛的发行版。"

#. translators: The distrowatch.com website is translated into many languages
#. (see http://distrowatch.com/dwres.php?resource=about). If your language is
#. present, please replace "EN" in the URL by the code of your language (e.g.
#. for Spanish, the last part would become "language=ES").
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:49
msgid ""
"Note: There are <a "
"href=\"http://distrowatch.com/dwres.php?resource=major&amp;language=EN\">plenty"
" of distributions to choose from and compare</a>."
msgstr "提示: 这里有<a href=\"http://distrowatch.com/dwres.php?resource=major&amp;language=EN\">大量的发行版供选择和比较</a>。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:50
msgid "This is our selection for newcomers. These links are not commercial."
msgstr "为新手提供参考，非商业推广。"

#. translators: use url of official localised Ubuntu homepage, if existing
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:58
msgid "http://www.ubuntu.com/"
msgstr "http://www.ubuntu.com/"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:61
msgid ""
"Simple, easy, usable and our personal favourite. A tanned, smooth atmosphere"
" that never gets in your way. All programs are kept in order and managed "
"easily. Configuration is kept simple rather than exhaustive."
msgstr "简单，容易，实用，是我们的最爱。铺展在你面前的是一片柔和与舒畅。所有的程序有条不紊，管理方便。配置文件简约而不冗赘。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:62
msgid ""
"We recommend this friendly and complete distribution if you are looking for "
"an easy way to try and step into GNU/Linux."
msgstr "如果您正在尝试进入 GNU/Linux，我们推荐这款友好、功能齐全的发行版。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:63
msgid ""
"Ubuntu also has a sister distribution, <a "
"href=\"http://www.kubuntu.org/\">Kubuntu</a>, with a different layout and "
"slightly more advanced graphics."
msgstr "Ubuntu还有一个具不同层次感和更高级图形的姐妹发行版，<a href=\"http://www.kubuntu.org/\">Kubuntu</a>"

#. translators: use url of official localised Fedora homepage, if existing
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:89
msgid "http://fedoraproject.org/"
msgstr "http://fedoraproject.org/"

#. translators: if you don't know of a clean, simple comparison website,
#. simply remove the link.
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:94
msgid ""
"The distribution by the long-time prominent GNU/Linux developer company Red "
"Hat. The default layout is similar to Ubuntu (it is also possible to use "
"KDE, the more advanced desktop environment in use in Kubuntu), but <a "
"href=\"http://polishlinux.org/choose/comparison/?distro1=Ubuntu&amp;distro2=Fedora\""
" title=\"What are the differences between Fedora and Ubuntu?\">there are "
"differences</a> in the chosen applications, install protocols and several "
"technical elements."
msgstr "然而你不应该把 Linux 想成是 Windows 的克隆。想知道使用它有什么值得期待，建议你阅读我们的<a href=\"%s\">转向</a>一页。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:95
msgid ""
"We recommend this distribution if you wish to learn more about the workings "
"of a GNU/Linux system, security configuration, or work on software "
"development."
msgstr "如果你想学习更多有关GNU/Linux系统如何工作，相关安全配置或者从事软件开发，我们推荐这款发行版。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:124
#, php-format
msgid ""
"While Ubuntu contains some restricting components (<a "
"href=\"%s#full_freedom\">why?</a>), the Trisquel developers have built an "
"entirely free derivative. Although its community is smaller and its hardware"
" support might be slightly inferior, Trisquel gives anyone full freedom over"
" a complete operating system similar to Ubuntu."
msgstr "因为 Ubuntu 包含一些受限制的部件(<a href=\"%s#full_freedom\">为什么?</a>)，Trisquel 的开发者需要构建全部的自由衍生品。虽然其社区不如 Ubuntu 般壮大，硬件的支持并不能那么全面，但却能给您提供一个与 Ubuntu 相似的、完全自由的操作系统。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:125
msgid ""
"We recommend this distribution if you are committed to freedom in your "
"computing."
msgstr "如果您非常看重计算自由，我们推荐这款发行版本。"

#. translators: We try to be friendly and inviting here. The term "get a CD"
#. does not have to be translated exactly.
#: pages/switch_to_linux.choose_a_distribution.php:153
msgid "Now get a CD and try or install your distribution!"
msgstr "那现在就获取一张CD，体验一下或者直接安装吧！"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:23
msgid ""
"This is what everyday users usually find better, mostly the same, or not as "
"good, when switching from Windows to Linux."
msgstr "这些是用户从 Windows 转到 Linux 后日常使用软件的比较。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:32
msgid "What is better in Linux"
msgstr "Linux 好在哪里"

#. translators: please note the punctuation should be consistent
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:37
msgid "It's free"
msgstr "自由"

#. translators: link to Free Software definition on GNU.org site, if
#. softwareliberty.com is not translated in your language
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:41
msgid ""
"Unlike Windows, GNU/Linux is <a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" "
"title=\"What does Free Software mean?\">free software</a> &ndash; free as in"
" freedom. Install it on all computers and make copies for your friends! You "
"can even study it, transform it as you please, or build and sell your own "
"distribution."
msgstr "与 Windows 不同，GNU/Linux 是<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"What does Free Software mean?\">自由软件(free software)</a> — 在所有的电脑上安装它，为你的朋友们制作副本！你可以学习它，定制它，或者构建及出售自己的发行版。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:45
msgid "Programs"
msgstr "程序"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:47
msgid ""
"There are a wealth of free applications available at no cost under Linux. To"
" edit professional documents, burn music CDs, rework photos, design a "
"website, or organise music; there's no need for $200 software with "
"restrictive licenses."
msgstr "在 Linux 下有丰富的免费软件可供您使用！比如编写论文、刻录音乐光盘、修整照片、设计网站或者整理音乐。您不需要购买一个价格高达200美元的、受限制的商业软件。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:48
msgid ""
"The internal installer makes it incredibly easy to find, install and remove "
"programs."
msgstr "内置的软件安装工具使得寻找、安装或移除程序变得异常简便。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:49
msgid ""
"It's also safe: you can forget the demo/trial crippled software, or harmful "
"freeware polluting the web."
msgstr "并且这很安全：您可以永远忘记那些残废的试用版软件，和泛滥于网络上的那些有害的免费软件。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:53
msgid "No fighting"
msgstr "不再挣扎"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:55
msgid ""
"Keeping your computer in shape over time needn't be a struggle. One year on,"
" GNU/Linux runs just as fast as the first day. And it may bring your old PC "
"back to life."
msgstr "让您的电脑青春常驻无须费功夫。一年之后，GNU/Linux跑起来还跟第一天那么快。它还有可能让您作古的PC起死回生。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:56
msgid ""
"Also, Linux lets you choose what you want and what you don't. If you had a "
"hard time getting rid of MSN Messenger, Windows Update notifications, or "
"Clippit the paperclip, you'll find it refreshing."
msgstr "并且Linux给予您选择是否使用一个软件的权力。如果您曾经被 MSN、Windows Update 通知或者Office大眼夹助手烦扰过，您会在 Linux 中找到属于您的清新。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:60
msgid "Security"
msgstr "安全"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:62
msgid ""
"Forget expensive and restrictive anti-virus, anti-spyware, anti-anything and"
" anti-everything. Linux is very, very secure."
msgstr "永远忘记一切昂贵的、受束缚的杀毒软件、安全助手和平时使用 Windows 的小心翼翼吧。Linux将会给您一个安全的世界。"

#. translators: If you don't know of a link replacement in your languge, just
#. leave the link as it is
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:64
msgid ""
"It is often difficult for Windows users to believe that there are <em>no "
"spyware nor viruses</em> under Linux &mdash; <a "
"href=\"http://linuxmafia.com/~rick/faq/index.php?page=virus#virus\">but it's"
" true</a>. Malicious programs have a hard time doing anything at all in a "
"well-built system."
msgstr "通常 Windows 用户都难以相信在 Linux 下<em>没有任何恶意软件和病毒</em>&mdash; <a href=\"http://linuxmafia.com/~rick/faq/index.php?page=virus#virus\">但这是现实</a>。恶意软件在一个坚固的操作系统下束手无策。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:65
msgid "Regular, easy software updates will keep everyone entirely safe."
msgstr "通常情况下，轻松完成的软件更新会让每个人都处于安全的保障下。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:69
msgid "Support"
msgstr "支持"

#. translators: The first %s represents the URL to the "More" page and seconds
#. %s represents the title of the page "More" in your language
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:72
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Linux benefits from a great sense of community whose friendliness will "
"surprise you. If you try to do something complicated but can't succeed, "
"there are a lot of people around to help you out. Our \"<a "
"href=\"%s\">%s</a>\" page gives a few pointers."
msgstr "Linux的优势来自于一群热心友善的社区成员，他们的亲切会让您感到无限的惊奇。如果您希望做一些复杂的事情却发现自己无能为力，在您身后，将会有无数的人愿意提供帮助。我们的“<a href=\"%s\">%s</a>”页面举出了几个例子。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:73
msgid ""
"The companies behind the main GNU/Linux distributions, such as <a "
"href=\"http://www.canonical.com/\">Canonical</a> and <a "
"href=\"http://www.redhat.com/\">Red Hat</a>, also provide expert commercial "
"support."
msgstr "在 GNU/Linux 发行版背后的那些公司——比如 <a href=\"http://www.canonical.com/\">Canonical</a> 和 <a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/\">Red Hat</a>——将会给您专家级的社区支持。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:82
msgid "What is mostly the same in Linux"
msgstr "在 Linux 中基本无差别"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:84
msgid ""
"Fundamentally, everyday users will find GNU/Linux similar in use to Windows "
"or Mac OSX."
msgstr "基本上，普通用户会发现GNU/Linux在使用上与Windows或者 Mac OSX 近似。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:87
msgid "General set-up"
msgstr "常规设置"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:89
msgid ""
"If you still believe Linux is controlled with code and command-line, you "
"should update your views!"
msgstr "如果仍然认为 Linux 是通过代码和命令控制的，请赶紧改变您的想法"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:90
msgid ""
"Just like Windows, Linux has to boot when you switch your computer on, and "
"then you use programs in it to do different things. The taskbar and layout "
"of applications will feel familiar to Windows or Mac OS users."
msgstr "就像Windows一样，Linux 在您打开您的计算机时需要引导启动，之后您就可以使用程序来做不同的事情。Linux的任务栏和布局会让 Windows 和 Mac OS 用户感到无比亲切。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:94
msgid "Web browsing and common tasks"
msgstr "网页浏览和一般任务"

#. translators: use localized Firefox landing page if possible
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:97
msgid ""
"The Web looks just the same when viewed with Linux (in fact you can browse "
"the Web with the same program if you already use <a "
"href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/\">Firefox</a> or <a "
"href=\"http://www.google.com/chrome/\">Google Chrome</a>). And of course, "
"you can go through your picture and music collection all the same. Files and"
" folders are navigated with a file manager like Windows Explorer."
msgstr "在 Linux 上看到的网页和 Windows 下完全相同（事实上您可以选择继续使用您已经在使用的软件如 <a href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/\">Firefox</a> 或者 <a href=\"http://www.google.com/chrome/\">Google Chrome</a>）。当然，您也可以像在Windows下一样查看您的照片，享受您的音乐。文件和文件夹的管理和Windows下的Explorer非常相似。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:106
msgid "What is not as good in Linux"
msgstr "Linux 做得还不够好"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:109
msgid "Driver support"
msgstr "驱动支持"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:111
msgid ""
"Manufacturers of computer hardware don't always (yet) release drivers for "
"Linux or publicize full specifications."
msgstr "计算机硬件制造商并不总(至少现在)放出 Linux 的驱动或者公开所有的技术规格，"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:112
msgid ""
"So, drivers are sometimes unavailable for the most recent high-end graphics "
"cards &mdash; some are reverse-engineered from Windows drivers by "
"volunteers. Some are also released free of charge, but under restrictive "
"licenses."
msgstr "所以有时您可能无法找到高端显卡的最新驱动&mdash;有些驱动是由志愿者们从 Windows 驱动反编译得来的，而有些驱动是免费，但不自由的。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:113
msgid "Sadly, the same problem occurs with many low-end WiFi cards."
msgstr "很不幸的，这个问题在一些低端无线网卡上也会出现。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:114
msgid ""
"However, the vast majority of computers with standard hardware work out of "
"the box with main Linux distributions. Common hardware such as USB keys or "
"photo cameras never are a problem."
msgstr ""
"不过，Linux 发行版可以在多数使用常见硬件的计算机下运行，通用硬件如U盘或者相机"
"的使用在 Linux 下从无问题。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:118
msgid "DVDs, restricted formats"
msgstr "受限制的DVD光盘"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:120
msgid ""
"Many multimedia formats in use are proprietary and not openly specified; "
"this means, broadly speaking, that Linux programmers have to find out how to"
" read them without any help from the format designers."
msgstr "不少多媒体格式是受版权限制的，没有完全公开，而原作者也不愿意帮助 Linux 开发者解决这些问题。也就是说，通常 Linux 开发者需要独立找出读取它们的方法。"

#. translators: Please choose the wording of the DRM acronym according to the
#. FSF terminology
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:122
msgid ""
"This might lead you to circumvent the restrictions in some DVDs and the "
"<abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions Management\">DRM</abbr> in some music "
"files, even if you purchased them in full legality, to be make them work "
"under Linux. Unfortunately, depending on where you live, <em>such "
"circumvention processes may be illegal</em> even if you purchased your media"
" entirely legally."
msgstr "这可能导致您尽管可能已经合法地购买了它们，却不得不绕开一些DVD的限制和一些音乐文件的 <abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions Management\">DRM</abbr>保护。很不幸，在一些地区<em>这种规避的行为可能是不合法的</em>，尽管您已经为它们付了钱。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:123
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:136
msgid "Read more in our Linux FAQ:"
msgstr "在 Linux FAQ 中了解更多："

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:131
msgid "Gaming"
msgstr "游戏"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:133
msgid ""
"Hard-core computer gamers, you might find that the Linux gaming world is "
"less professional and out-of-the-box than under Windows: the large game "
"developing companies are only slowly getting interested in the free software"
" world, which means that many well-known titles do not work on Linux, or "
"need special restrictive emulators to work."
msgstr "死忠的计算机游戏者们，可能要让您失望了——在 Linux 下您会发现这个操作系统下的游戏有些不够专业或者过时了。游戏公司还没有对自由软件世界提起兴趣，许多知名的游戏或不能在 Linux 下运行，或者需要受限制的模拟器。"

#. translators: use localised link if possible, and contact us if you know
#. better resources
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:135
msgid ""
"There is a very active free software game development community though, and "
"they have produced quite a few high-quality games, both 2D and 3D, that are "
"free software. You can head to the <a "
"href=\"http://ubuntuforums.org/forumdisplay.php?f=93\">Ubuntu gaming "
"forum</a> to find more information."
msgstr "但是在这个自由的世界，有一群向往自由的游戏开发者为自己的梦想奋斗着，他们开发了一些高质量的游戏，除了2D外也不乏3D的作品，并且都是自由的！你可以在 <a href=\"http://ubuntuforums.org/forumdisplay.php?f=93\">Ubuntu游戏论坛</a>了解更多的信息。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:144
msgid "Hibernating"
msgstr "休眠"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:146
msgid ""
"Because of the driver issues above, hibernating is not always reliable. The "
"most common occurrence is the loss of WiFi connection after hibernating on "
"laptops whose hardware drivers are not free."
msgstr "因为上面所述的问题，休眠并不总是稳定的。如果您笔记本的驱动不是自由的，在休眠后您可能会断开与无线网络的连接。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:155
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr "结论"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:157
msgid ""
"Whether you are going to enjoy Linux depends mostly on what you expect from "
"it."
msgstr "如果 Linux的特性正好能满足您的需求，恭喜您，您将在这个自由的世界里找到乐趣："

#. translators: Use a localised version of the "Linux is Not Windows" article
#. if possible. The following page contains links to localised versions:
#. http://geekblog.oneandoneis2.org/index.php/2005/12/31/derived_works_aamp_translations
#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:162
msgid ""
"If you wish Linux to be just exactly like Windows, you will probably be "
"disappointed. GNU/Linux is built by people who simply <a "
"href=\"http://linux.oneandoneis2.org/LNW.htm\">wish it to be different</a>. "
"In the free software community, members have different visions of what makes"
" an ideal operating system. These differences lead to variety, which is what"
" makes Linux so special and interesting."
msgstr "如果您希望 Linux 与 Windows 完全相同，您可能会失望了。GNU/Linux 是由一群<a href=\"http://linux.oneandoneis2.org/LNW.htm\">希望有所个性</a>的人建立的。在开源社区中，每个人都有对理想操作系统的不同的向往，也正是因为这样，才有了五彩斑斓的 Linux 世界。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:165
msgid ""
"Your freedom matters. Thousands in communities and companies work to build "
"software on which you may exert this freedom. Using GNU/Linux is the easiest"
" way to do so fully."
msgstr "您的自由是我们最大的希望。千千万万的社区和公司为了您对自由的需求不懈奋斗着。使用 GNU/Linux 会让您感受到真正的自由。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:168
msgid ""
"It's fun! Not having to worry about spyware, viruses, program registrations,"
" demos that expire, or finding software that is really free as in freedom, "
"makes using a computer suddenly very enjoyable."
msgstr "这太有趣了！希望拥有这样一个操作系统吗？——没有任何恶意软件，没有任何病毒，没有注册，没有试用！自由地寻找自由的软件吧，让使用计算机突然充满乐趣！"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:172
msgid ""
"We hope you'll switch soon. There's a large community waiting, and no one in"
" it asking you to &quot;sign up, purchase and register&quot;."
msgstr "我们期待着您来到 Linux 阵营中，这里广大的社区在等待着您。没有人会要求您购买，没有人会强迫您注册！"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:182
#: pages/switch_to_linux.php:41
msgid "Our selection for an easy choice."
msgstr "我们提供的一个简单选择。"

#. translators: please note the "affirmative" tone with the '.' at end of
#. sentence.
#: pages/switch_to_linux.php:27
msgid "Meet GNU/Linux in everyday use."
msgstr "日常使用 GNU/Linux"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.php:55
msgid "Install it! (it's easier than you think)"
msgstr "安装吧！（远比你想象的容易）"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:23
msgid ""
"Make the step &ndash; unless you wish to <a "
"href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/\" title=\"Linux Desktops and "
"Laptops\">purchase a PC with Linux pre-installed</a>, you can see what "
"freedom looks like on your computer."
msgstr "按照下面的步骤&ndash;除非您希望<a href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/\" title=\"Linux台式机和笔记本\">购买一台预装了 Linux的计算机</a>&ndash;您会感受到您的计算机给您带来的自由的乐趣。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:30
msgid "Try out: the live CD"
msgstr "试用：live CD"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:32
msgid "Take no risk"
msgstr "无需冒险"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:36
msgid ""
"Using a live CD means that Linux will be running on your computer "
"<em>without installing anything</em>. It's a risk-less way to try and see by"
" yourself what Linux is."
msgstr "使用live CD意即<em>在不安装任何东西的情况下</em>让Linux在你的电脑上运行。这是你尝试体验Linux的一个无风险方案。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:37
msgid ""
"When running on a live CD, your computer uses solely the CD-ROM to work "
"(without accessing the hard drive inside). You can launch all of the default"
" programs, edit documents, and browse the web."
msgstr "当您运行在一个 live CD 上时，并不会修改您硬盘上的任何东西(仅仅使用您的光驱)。您可以运行所有的默认软件、编辑文档或者浏览网页。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:38
msgid ""
"Since it is only designed as a trial mode, it is a little slow (it will take"
" you five minutes to boot up, and programs launch somewhat slowly). If you "
"proceed to install, the system will go much faster."
msgstr "因为这被设计为试用模式，所以可能有一点点慢(您可能需要几分钟的时间来启动操作系统，并且运行软件会有点慢)。如果您安装在您的计算机上会快很多。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:40
#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:54
msgid "What you need"
msgstr "需要什么"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:42
msgid ""
"To use a live CD, you need a little bit of curiosity and fifteen minutes of "
"free time, but <strong>no advanced knowledge in computing</strong>. If you "
"feel confident simply using Windows from time to time, then this is within "
"your reach."
msgstr "使用一个 live CD 只需要您有一点点的好奇心和几十分钟的空闲时间， <strong>并不需要您对计算机有专业了解</strong>。如果您在日常生活中能够简单地使用 Windows操作系统，那么这对您来说也是简单至极。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:48
msgid "Installing as a dual boot"
msgstr "安装成双启动"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:50
msgid "Choose at start-up"
msgstr "开始时的选择"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:51
msgid ""
"It is possible to install GNU/Linux along with Windows. This means that upon"
" start-up, you will be greeted with a screen allowing you to boot into the "
"operating system you prefer."
msgstr "安装Linux使之与Windows共存也是可能的。这样，在你开启的时候，你会从屏幕上得到提示，让你可以导入你偏爱的操作系统。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:52
msgid ""
"Setting up a dual-boot can be helpful if you need time to abandon "
"restrictive software. It is <a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop"
"/install-desktop-latest\" title=\"a tutorial on installing Ubuntu\">not "
"difficult to set-up</a>, though erasing Windows altogether is even easier."
msgstr "如果摈弃限制性的软件需要时间，您可以选择安装双系统， <a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/install-desktop-latest\" title=\"安装 Ubuntu 的指南\">而这并不困难</a>，虽然将 Windows 彻底删去会更加简单。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:55
msgid ""
"Installing Linux on your computer will take you less than 30 minutes. It is "
"not an obvious step for complete beginners, but if you use computers on a "
"daily basis this is very likely within your reach. If you have already re-"
"installed Windows on your computer, rest assured that installing Linux is no"
" harder."
msgstr "在你的电脑上安装Linux只会花掉你不到30分钟的时间。这对完完全全的初学者来讲并不是一个明白的举动，但如果你每天都用电脑，这应该也在你力所能及的范围之内。如果你已经在你的电脑上重装过Windows，那就放心吧，安装Linux定不难于此。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:61
msgid "Get the CD or DVD you need"
msgstr "获取需要的 CD 或 DVD"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:63
msgid ""
"For the distributions we recommend, the live CD/DVD is the same as the "
"installation CD/DVD. You can either download and burn a CD/DVD yourself, or "
"order a CD/DVD from a trusted vendor."
msgstr "对于我们推荐的这些发行版而言，Live CD/DVD 和安装 CD/DVD 是相同的。您可以自己下载并刻录一张，或者从您信任的发行商手中获取这些 CD/DVD。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:68
msgid ""
"You can download an <code>iso</code> image (rather large file) and then <a "
"href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/burn-a-dvd-on-windows\">burn "
"it to a CD or DVD</a>. Once the CD/DVD is burned, you can use it to <a "
"href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/install-desktop-"
"latest\">install Ubuntu</a> onto your computer."
msgstr "您可以下载 <code>iso</code> 镜像 (而不是巨大的文件) 然后<a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/burn-a-dvd-on-windows\">刻录一张 CD 或者 DVD</a>。之后您便可以<a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/install-desktop-latest\">将 Ubuntu 安装进您的电脑</a>。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:72
msgid "Download Ubuntu"
msgstr "下载 Ubuntu"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:75
#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:91
#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:107
msgid "Order a CD/DVD"
msgstr "订购一张 CD/DVD"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:84
msgid ""
"The Fedora live CD/DVD also enables installation. Follow the <a "
"href=\"http://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-"
"US/Fedora/18/html/Installation_Quick_Start_Guide/index.html\">installation "
"quick start guide</a> to get started with Fedora."
msgstr "Fedora 的 Live CD/DVD 同时也可以用于安装。您可以根据 <a href=\"http://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/Fedora/18/html/Installation_Quick_Start_Guide/index.html\">快速安装指南</a> 开始使用 Fedora。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:88
msgid "Download Fedora"
msgstr "下载 Fedora"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:100
msgid ""
"The <a href=\"http://trisquel.info/en/wiki/installation-guide\">Trisquel "
"installation</a> is very similar to that of Ubuntu."
msgstr "<a href=\"http://trisquel.info/en/wiki/installation-guide\">Trisquel 的安装</a>与 Ubuntu 非常相似。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:104
msgid "Download Trisquel"
msgstr "下载 Trisquel"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:113
msgid ""
"Note: Purchased and downloaded CDs are identical! GNU/Linux is <a "
"href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"What do you mean, "
"free?\">free software</a>. You are simply paying a handling/shipping fee."
msgstr "注: 购买一个光盘和下载一个镜像是一样的！GNU/Linux 是<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"什么？自由免费？\">免费的自由软件</a>——当然如果您需要一张光盘，我们只收取邮寄的费用。"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:120
msgid "Free Software pre-installed"
msgstr "预装的自由软件"

#: pages/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:122
msgid ""
"Not all computers are shipped with Windows. If you do not wish to make the install yourself, or are in need of new hardware, you can get a laptop or a desktop pre-installed with GNU/Linux.<br/>\n"
"We have compiled <a title=\"linux computers\" href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/\">a list of vendors pre-installing Linux at LinuxPreloaded.com</a> just for that reason."
msgstr "并不是所有的计算机都是附带着 Windows 销售的。如果您并不想自己安装，或者您正好需要购买新的计算机，您可以选择购买一台预装着GNU/Linux的台式机或者笔记本。我们为您列出了<a title=\"linux computers\" href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/\">一个预装Linux操作系统的计算机厂商列表</a>。"

#. translators: This is the catcher-phrase for the Windows page. Exact
#. translation is not required, the goal is to attract attention and set the
#. tone of the page.
#: pages/windows.php:21
msgid "Windows and Office work fine &mdash; Why worry about it?"
msgstr "Windows和Office用得好好的，担心什么呢？"

#. translators: You may add emphasis ('em' tags) around the word 'licensed' if
#. you wish
#: pages/windows.php:29
msgid ""
"A legal copy of Windows is expensive, but what do you get? Windows and "
"Office are licensed, not sold."
msgstr "一个正版的Windows那么昂贵，但是您得到了什么呢？Windows和Office是注册许可的，并不出售。"

#: pages/windows.php:31
msgid ""
"By using these products, we have to agree to <strong>a number of harsh "
"restrictions</strong>. For most Windows licenses, you can't keep the "
"software when you change the hardware. You sometimes can't even give your "
"software away. Who can run the software? On which computer? What can you do "
"with it? The list of restrictions is long and some items are outrageous."
msgstr "要用这些产品，我们得同意<strong>一系列的严格限制</strong>。对大多数的Windows协议，当变更硬件的时候您并不能保留软件。有的时候，您甚至不能送出您购买的软件。谁能运行该软件？运行在哪台计算机上？您能做什么？那张满是限制的表单奇长无比，而且一些条款简直不可理喻。"

#: pages/windows.php:39
msgid "Software should come without locks in it."
msgstr "软件应该不带任何枷锁地发布。"

#: pages/windows.php:41
msgid ""
"Why are Office documents difficult to export? Why are the formats "
"continually changing? Why can you not even uninstall some programs? It might"
" be that if you look for choice, Microsoft products aren't for you."
msgstr "为什么Office文档难于导出呢？为什么它的格式持续变更呢？更有甚者，您无法卸载一些程序。如果您希望有更多选择的余地，那么Microsoft的产品可能不适合您。"

#: pages/windows.php:49
msgid ""
"The source codes of Windows and Office are hidden, so, <strong>no one is "
"allowed to understand</strong> how these programs work."
msgstr "Windows和Office的源代码不可见，因此，<strong>不允许任何人去理解</strong>这些程序是如何运作的。"

#: pages/windows.php:51
msgid ""
"If you can't get a right to inspect source code (the human-readable inner "
"workings of a program), you can't have someone correct flaws or evaluate how"
" your privacy is protected for you."
msgstr "倘若您不能获得检视源代码（一个程序的内部机理）的权利，您就不能让专业人士修补缺陷或评估您的隐私是否受到保护。"

#: pages/windows.php:53
msgid ""
"And guess what? On software that comes with source code, viruses and spyware"
" aren't effective, and security isn't bought on extra. The antivirus "
"software industry, in which Microsoft is now a significant player, prefers "
"you to use Windows."
msgstr "猜怎么着？病毒对那些与源代码一同发布的软件失效了，您不比为安全额外破费。反病毒产业是特别希望你用 Windows 的，Microsoft 在这里面可是一个重要角色。"

#. translators: In your language, you might not need to make the distinction
#. between price and freedom. Please do however express that price does not
#. matter, in this sentence.
#: pages/windows.php:63
msgid ""
"A free society requires free software. Think of &quot;free&quot; as in "
"freedom, not price: the freedoms to inspect, learn from, modify the software"
" you use."
msgstr "一个自由的社区需要自由的软件。想想这样一个自由的世界吧——您可以自由地查看软件的每个细节、从中学习甚至自由修改您使用的软件。"

#: pages/windows.php:65
msgid ""
"Computers are used to share ideas, culture and information. Without these "
"freedoms over software, we risk losing control over what we share."
msgstr "计算机是用来分享观点，文化和信息的。如若没有软件上的这些自由，我们则将承担对这些分享品失去掌控的风险。"

#: pages/windows.php:67
msgid ""
"This is happening today. From plain annoying technologies such as Digital "
"Restrictions Management (<strong>DRM</strong>) to downright frightening ones"
" like <strong>Trusted Computing</strong>, everyone's ability to participate "
"in culture is threatened."
msgstr "而这一切现在正在发生。种种技术，从明显恼人的如数字约束管理（<strong>DRM</strong>）到十分吓人的如<strong>可信计算</strong>，每个人参与文化的权利都在受到来自它们的威胁。"

#: pages/windows.php:69
msgid ""
"If you have to give up your freedoms to use software, maybe you should not "
"be happy with it."
msgstr "如果您得放弃自由才能用上这些软件，兴许您该不高兴了吧。"

#. translators: This is the conclusion of the article.
#: pages/windows.php:81
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Many people find that Windows, an otherwise decent piece of software, "
"<strong>withdraws so many rights</strong> from them, that it is not worth "
"them using it. Mac&nbsp;OS is <a href=\"%s#mac_freedom\">not much "
"better</a>, either."
msgstr "许多人都发现，视窗操作系统虽然是非常优秀的软件，却<strong>剥夺了用户太多的权利</strong> 所以不值得使用。Mac&nbsp;OS 也 <a href=\"%s#mac_freedom\">没有好到哪里</a>。"

#: pages/windows.php:83
#, php-format
msgid ""
"If you find <a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"what is "
"freedom in software?\">free software</a> attractive, you might want to <a "
"href=\"%s\" title=\"make the switch to Linux today!\">give Linux a try</a>."
msgstr "如果您觉得<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"what is freedom in software?\">自由软件</a> 很有吸引力，那你也许想<a href=\"%s\" title=\"make the switch to Linux today!\">尝试一下Linux</a>吧。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:22
#, php-format
msgid ""
"We wished to keep our \"<a href=\"%s\">Restrictions</a>\" page short, so we "
"moved many of the license restrictions out here. Here is the fine print "
"inside the Microsoft licenses."
msgstr "我们希望我们的\"<a href=\"%s\">限制</a>\"页面尽量简短，所以我们把许多的许可证限制移到了这里。这些是微软许可证内的细节："

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:26
msgid "It is unclear who can use, receive or buy your software."
msgstr "谁可以使用、接收或者购买您拥有的软件由微软说的算"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:28
msgid ""
"The license is particularly unclear as to who may or may not use your "
"version of Windows or Office. Several sentences in the Microsoft Office "
"license suggest it would be illegal to let your neighbour type a letter with"
" your version of Word on your computer."
msgstr "这份许可证在谁可以或者谁不可以使用您的 Windows 或者 Office 的问题上含糊不清。在 Microsoft Office 许可证中的几个句子表明了您的邻居使用您计算机上的 Word 程序打一封信是非法行为。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:30
msgid ""
"It is however clear in the Microsoft Windows license that you may "
"<em>only</em> give or sell your copy of Windows software to anyone "
"<strong>if you are the first buyer</strong>. This means, that if you buy it "
"from the user who initially purchased it from Microsoft, then <em>you</em> "
"are not able to sell or give the software away to yet another user, even if "
"you do not use it anymore, even if you buy the latest software version with "
"your new computer."
msgstr "非常明显的，根据 Microsoft Windows 许可证，您<em>只</em>可以在您<strong>从微软处获得此拷贝的情况下</strong>将其出售。也就意味着，如果您的操作系统是二手的或者您的操作系统被预装于计算机中，您就不能将其转售，即使您再也不使用它。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:34
msgid ""
"You may not lease, lend or provide commercial hosting services with the "
"software"
msgstr "您不能将这个软件租借出去或者用其提供商业服务"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:36
msgid ""
"You cannot let professional users use your software, whether they pay for "
"the service or not, and whether you use a &quot;Professional&quot; license "
"or not."
msgstr "您不能让专业人士使用您的软件：无论他们是否购买过，也无论您是否拥有一个&quot;专业&quot;授权。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:40
msgid "The upgrade is only valid for the first license you use it on"
msgstr "您只能在您第一台授权的计算机上享受更新"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:42
msgid ""
"If that original license expires (for example because the computer it came "
"on stops working), so does the upgrade. If you purchase an upgrade, you are "
"not allowed to use the original software version anymore."
msgstr "如果最初的授权过期了(比如因为您的计算机坏了)，那么您也将永久失去您的更新。如果您为升级付了款，原有的旧软件您也无法再使用。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:46
msgid "Educational versions are crippled"
msgstr "教育版是残废的"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:48
msgid ""
"If Microsoft accepts to define you as a student or an academic, you are "
"allowed to buy an academic license, and install the software on three "
"computers. But it is illegal to use it for any commercial purpose \"<em>or "
"in any way related to the operation of any business enterprise or revenue-"
"generating activities</em>\"."
msgstr "如果微软承认您是一位学生或者学者，您将可以购买一份教育授权，并在三台计算机上安装此授权。但任何商业用途的使用\"<em>或者一切与商业或者盈利相关的活动</em>\"都是非法的。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:52
msgid "The components of the software may not be separated"
msgstr "软件中的任何部件都是不可分离的"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:54
msgid ""
"It is illegal to buy Microsoft Office, then install only Word on one "
"computer, and only Excel on another. The Office suite is one single product."
msgstr "购买 Microsoft Office 后，如果您在一台计算机上安装Word而在另一台计算机上安装 Excel，您可能会收到一张法院的传单。Office 套件是一个单独的产品。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:58
msgid "Private information is collected"
msgstr "收集隐私信息"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:60
msgid ""
"The licence explicitly states that \"Microsoft and its affiliates\" collect "
"technical information gathered on your computer by the software. They "
"\"<em>may use this information solely to improve products or to provide "
"customized services or technologies</em>\"."
msgstr "许可证中明确写道：“微软和其分支机构”可以通过此软件收集您计算机上的技术信息。他们“<em>仅将此信息用于改善他们的产品或者提供个性化服务或者技术支持</em>”。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:62
msgid ""
"In order to activate most Microsoft products, as part of the license "
"agreement, your computer connects to the Microsoft servers and sends "
"&quot;technical&quot; information. It can &quot;solely&quot; be used for "
"pretty much anything."
msgstr "作为许可证协议中的一部分内容，为了激活绝大多数的微软产品，您的计算机将会被连接到微软服务器并传送一些“技术”信息。他们“仅仅”可以被用于做许多的事情。"

#. translators: If it exists, please use a non-official translation of the GPL
#. in your language, as pointed on
#. http://www.gnu.org/licenses/translations.html
#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:72
msgid "http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html"
msgstr "http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:72
msgid "The GNU General Public License"
msgstr "GNU通用公共许可证(GPL)"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:72
msgid "The GPL"
msgstr "GPL"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:74
msgid ""
"The GNU General Public License, under which GNU/Linux and a vast amount of "
"free software are published."
msgstr "GNU/Linux 和很多很多的自由软件都是在GNU通用公共许可证下发布的"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:76
msgid "Comparing the GPL to the Microsoft WinXP License"
msgstr "将 GPL 与 WinXP的协议对比"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:78
msgid ""
"A thorough and clear comparison of the <abbr title=\"GNU General Public "
"License\">GPL</abbr> and the Microsoft <abbr title=\"End-User License "
"Agreement\">EULA</abbr> license that governs the use of most Windows XP "
"versions."
msgstr "在<abbr title=\"GNU通用公共许可证\">GPL</abbr>和微软<abbr title=\"最终用户许可协议\">EULA</abbr>(被用于绝大多数的Windows XP系统)间的一个深入但清晰的比较。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:81
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:137
msgid "http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/right-to-read.html"
msgstr "http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/right-to-read.html"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:81
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:137
msgid "The Right to Read"
msgstr "阅读的权力"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:83
msgid ""
"A short story by Richard Stallman that describes what influence restrictive "
"licenses could have on our lives."
msgstr "一个由 Richard Stallman 编写的，阐述受限许可证会对我们的生活造成怎样影响的，简短的故事"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:23
msgid ""
"A common mistake is for Windows and Office users to think that they fully "
"own their software. In fact, there are a number of <strong>legal "
"bindings</strong> applied to it."
msgstr "在 Windows 和 Office 用户间的一个普遍误解是他们完全拥有了他们购买的软件。但事实上，有一部分法律约束着他们。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:24
msgid "Haven't read your license fully? We did that job for you."
msgstr "您没有完全读过您的许可证吗？让我们来帮你完成这项工作吧。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:27
msgid "The small print in the contract"
msgstr "N+1号字的协议"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:31
msgid "Windows and Office are licensed, not sold."
msgstr "Windows 和 Ofiice 是授权给您使用，而不是出售。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:32
msgid ""
"No one can buy Windows or Microsoft Office: instead users <strong>purchase a"
" permission to use</strong> them. The license describes the terms of this "
"permission. It is the restrictive legal text you have to click \"OK\" to "
"upon install."
msgstr "没有人能够购买 Windows 或者 Microsoft Office：用户只是<strong>购买了使用他们的许可</strong>。这是一份充满限制的许可，但您只能选择“接受”。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:35
msgid "You must abandon many rights to use the software."
msgstr "使用这个软件，您可能要放弃很多的权利"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:36
msgid "There are a number of restrictions that you must accept by law."
msgstr "在法律上，有许多的限制您必须接受。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:37
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Restrictions on who can use the software, what kind of revenue you may earn "
"with it, on how you choose to install it, restrictions on your privacy, even"
" on whether you can give it away: the list is long. <a href=\"%s\" title=\"a"
" few more things about Microsoft licenses\">Reading the license and "
"enumerating your remaining rights</a> is itself a difficult task."
msgstr "谁可以使用这个软件，您可以从中获得怎样的收益，或者您如何安装此软件，您的隐私将会怎样被使用，甚至您是否可以将它送给别人——这个许可证协议上充满了限制，而且很长。从中<a href=\"%s\" title=\"更多关于微软许可证的信息\">了解您所剩不多的权利</a>是一项艰难的工作。"

#. translators: Don't bother with the 'abbr' code. You can tranlsate as 'OEM
#. [pre-installed]'
#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:44
msgid ""
"An <abbr title=\"Original Equipment Manufacturer (simply the hardware "
"seller)\">OEM</abbr>-distributed software cannot be transferred to another "
"computer."
msgstr "一个<abbr title=\"原始设备制造商\">OEM</abbr>版本软件不能被安装在另一台计算机上。"

#. translators: Don't bother with the 'shrink-wrap' expression. You can skip
#. that bit if you wish.
#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:48
msgid ""
"If you bought your computer with Windows or Office pre-installed (the so-"
"called OEM licenses, or the \"shrink wrap\" Windows discs), <strong>if you "
"change computers you must buy software again.</strong>"
msgstr "如果您购买了一台预装 Windows 或者 Ofiice 的计算机（也就是所谓的OEM授权，或者“缩水”的 Windows光盘），<strong>如果您更换了计算机您就不得不再购买一份授权</strong>。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:49
msgid ""
"The license is linked to one computer, and expires when the computer dies. "
"It is then illegal to transfer the software on another computer."
msgstr "这份授权与您的计算机紧紧地绑在一起，与您的计算机同生死共存亡。如果您希望将它安装在另外一台计算机上，很不幸，这是非法的。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:56
msgid ""
"If you go to most of the free software sites you can click down a couple of "
"levels and find the [GNU] <abbr title=\"General Public License, the main "
"free software license\">GPL</abbr>, the X license, the Apache license, "
"whichever terms and conditions you have to accept in order to use that "
"software."
msgstr "如果您访问大多数的自由软件网站，您可以找到[GNU] <abbr title=\"通用公共许可证，大多数自由软件使用的许可协议\">GPL</abbr>，X许可证和Apache许可证等。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:57
msgid ""
"Now with a proprietary software company, the license is buried so you can't "
"read it until after you have paid for the product, then they're asking you "
"to <strong>turn off part of your brain</strong>, they're asking you to turn "
"off part of your ability to work with other people and to do business, when "
"you use their software."
msgstr "许多拥有所有权的公司将许可证藏起来不让您看见，当您为产品付费后，他们会用许可证来要要挟您<strong>封锁您大脑的创意</strong>或者绑架您一部分能力，除非您不打算使用购买了的软件。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:58
msgid "Don Marti interview"
msgstr "Don Marti 访谈"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:58
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:34
msgid "2005 interview"
msgstr "2005年的访谈"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:61
msgid "The meaning behind"
msgstr "背后的意义"

#. translators: Please don't forget the rel=nofollow element in the link - it
#. makes sure we don't increase MS PR.
#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:65
msgid ""
"Companies like Microsoft like to assimilate their software to physical "
"products, <a href=\"http://www.microsoft.com/piracy/\" rel=\"nofollow\">when"
" mentioning copyright infringement</a> for example. Yet, proprietary "
"software is very different because of the restrictive license -such "
"restrictions would be unthinkable on a car or bicycle, for example."
msgstr "因为如<a href=\"http://www.microsoft.com/piracy/\" rel=\"nofollow\">受到版权侵害</a>等原因，像微软这样的软件公司就会寻求软件与硬件产品的绑定。因为受限制的许可证——这在一辆汽车或是自行车上简直不可原谅——版权保护的软件非常不同。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:66
msgid ""
"Restrictions on the use of Office and Windows are so harsh, that many "
"violations occur everyday around us. People are tempted to buy only one "
"version of Microsoft Office and install it on two computers. Others keep "
"their version of Windows when they throw their PC away. Other people give "
"away their second-hand Windows software when they stop using it."
msgstr "使用 Office 和 Windows 的限制是非常苛刻的，所以许多侵权事件在我们日常生活中经常发生。人们抵制不住购买一份 Microsoft Office 授权而在两台计算机上安装的诱惑，还有一些人在丢掉旧的计算机后保留了原有的那份 Windows 拷贝，或者在停止使用 Windows 时转让了他们的二手 Windows 软件。"

#. translators: use the definition of "free software" on GNU.org in place of
#. softwareliberty.com ; also, if you can, use a translation of the GPL as
#. found on http://www.gnu.org/licenses/translations.html
#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:69
msgid ""
"<strong>You have an alternative to breaking this law,</strong> or feeling "
"very restrained when you abide to it. GNU/Linux is <a "
"href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\">Free Software</a> (much better than"
" just freeware): its <a "
"href=\"http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html\">GPL</a> license is designed to"
" protect your rights."
msgstr "如果您对这些限制感到十分拘束，<strong>那么就投奔自由软件阵营吧</strong>。GNU/Linux 是<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\">一个自由且免费的软件</a>(比免费软件好多了)：他使用的<a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html\">GPL</a>许可证被用于保护您的权利。"

#: pages/windows.restrictions.php:71
msgid "Restrictions - further details"
msgstr "限制 — 详情信息"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:23
msgid "Stand for a Free Society"
msgstr "代表自由社区"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:26
msgid ""
"There is much more to software than being trustworthy (being \"Open-"
"Source\"): what really counts is <strong>the freedoms you get</strong> over "
"it. Can you learn from it? Can you build upon it? Can you distribute it? "
"That's what we refer to as \"free software\"."
msgstr "有很多的软件值得被信任: 真正重要的是通过它<strong>您能获得的自由</strong>。您是否能从中学习？您是否能在它上面继续构建？您是否能分发它？这就是我们所说的“自由软件”"

#. translators: This is the quote by Don Marti at the start of the article.
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:32
msgid ""
"I come up with new words, phrases, analogies, all kinds of fun stuff in the "
"English language and people paraphrase what I had to say and make money "
"talking about some of the same things that I did."
msgstr "我想出了新的词语、短语和类比，人们却意译我说过的话，通过谈论我做过的事情来赚钱。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:33
msgid ""
"<strong>If I try to lock down</strong> what I talk about and write about, "
"the same way as a proprietary software company does, then the whole industry"
" of speaking, writing, media, would be overly litigious, and transaction "
"costs would be prohibitive."
msgstr "如果您觉得<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"what is freedom in software?\">自由软件</a> 很有吸引力，那你也许想<a href=\"%s\" title=\"make the switch to Linux today!\">尝试一下Linux</a>吧。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:37
msgid "Not a crazy concept"
msgstr "并不是疯狂的概念"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:39
msgid ""
"It sounds peculiar to many users that software should be free as in freedom,"
" since none of Microsoft's products are. Yet our society works with many "
"free things in it, for example:"
msgstr "对于很多的用户来说这种软件的自由可能听起来很奇特——微软的任何一个产品都不曾有过这种自由。我们的社区正在为这种自由做着很多的事情，比如说："

#. translators: This is the short quote on the side of the article.
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:44
msgid ""
"Though no one has a proprietary lock on yoga, it is still a thriving $30 "
"billion business in the United States."
msgstr "因为没有人受到所有权的枷锁，瑜伽在美国仍是一个产值超30亿美元的兴旺产业。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:49
msgid ""
"No chef would ever forbid you to modify his recipe and make derivatives out "
"of it. The food industry thrives despite being required by law to list "
"ingredients on product labels."
msgstr "没有人会阻止您修改他菜谱，并对其进行派生。根据法律规定产品的配料被列在商品标签上，餐饮行业却也能蓬勃发展。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:50
msgid ""
"A fair law court system permits anyone to read through all the trial "
"hearings and arguments. Not only the result (the final deliberations), but "
"also the process is fully open."
msgstr "一个公平的法庭体系会允许任何人通读所有听审和论据，而不仅仅是结果（最后的审议结果），而且这个过程是完全开放的。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:53
msgid ""
"Free software is free as in &quot;free speech&quot;, as in a &quot;free "
"market&quot;: all are necessary for a free society. Unconvinced? Let us look"
" at proprietary software a little closer."
msgstr "自由软件不仅在“言论”上是自由的，还在“市场”上拥有自由——这些在自由的社会上都是必须的。不服气？让我们再看看专有软件吧。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:55
msgid "Proprietary software going wrong"
msgstr "私有软件错了"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:57
#, php-format
msgid ""
"The limits of proprietary software go beyond the security issue (see <a "
"href=\"%s\">our article on source code</a>): today proprietary software "
"interferes with the spread of culture and information. This happens mainly "
"through two technologies:"
msgstr "专有软件的限制超越了安全问题(浏览<a href=\"%s\">我们关于源代码问题的文章</a>)：今天专有软件对文化与信息自由传播的干扰，主要采用下列两种技术："

#. translators: This is sometimes only known as "DRM" in some languages.
#. Please choose the vocabulary carefully. The %s placeholder links to a
#. footnote which explains why we use the term "Digital Restrictions
#. Management":
#. http://www.getgnulinux.org/windows/stand_for_a_free_society/#footnote_bottom1
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:62
#, php-format
msgid "Digital Restrictions Management %s (DRM)"
msgstr "数字限制管理 %s (DRM)"

#. translators: The %s placeholder will automatically point to the footnote on
#. bottom of page
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:66
#, php-format
msgid ""
"The main idea of DRM %s is to restrict access to files. Users encounter this"
" when, for example, they purchase music through iTunes, and then can only "
"play their music with one player, from one brand. With this method, "
"companies fight copyright infringement, but they also severely restrain "
"users' access to their files."
msgstr "DRM %s 的主要想法是限制对文件的访问。比如用户在 iTunes 上购买音乐时便会发现他们只能在自己的播放器上播放这些音乐。通过这种手段，音乐公司成功地打击了版权侵害，但同时也严重损害了用户访问文件的权利。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:70
msgid "DRM is control over content"
msgstr "DRM 是对内容的控制"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:73
msgid ""
"Except that the control is not in the hands of the end-user. The original "
"purpose of <abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions Management\">DRM</abbr> is "
"understandable, but the implications over the flow of information and "
"culture within a society are frightening."
msgstr "除了对用户控制文件的权利的侵害，<abbr title=\"数字版权管理\">DRM</abbr>的初衷是可以理解的，但是对于信息与文化的传播的危害却是不可估量的。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:77
msgid ""
"Imagine a book that automatically became glued shut after you read it once."
msgstr "想象您购买了这样一本书，当您阅读一遍之后他会自动把每页粘在一起防止您把它和其他人分享。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:78
msgid ""
"Imagine documents that self-destructed if you tried to take them out of the "
"room."
msgstr "想象这样的一份文档，当您想要把它带出您的房间时它会自动销毁自己。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:79
msgid ""
"Imagine telephones that only worked if the person you were ringing was "
"renting the same make and model."
msgstr "想象这样一台电话机，只有当您呼叫同样牌子电话的人时才能工作。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:83
msgid "Sounds crazy? This is where Trusted Computing comes in."
msgstr "听起来很疯狂吧？这就是可信计算(TC)。"

#. translators: This is sometimes only known as "Trusted Computing", not TC,
#. in some languages. Please choose the vocabulary carefully.
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:87
msgid "Trusted Computing (TC)"
msgstr "可信计算(TC)"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:89
msgid ""
"Trusted Computing (sometimes <a href=\"http://www.lafkon.net/tc/\" title=\"A"
" very well done video on Trusted Computing\">more accurately</a> called "
"\"Treacherous Computing\") means a computer can only run \"Trusted\" "
"Software. It is meant to be an uncircumventable protection against nuisances"
" (like viruses or spyware) and copyright violations (people copying "
"proprietary software)."
msgstr "可信计算(或者<a href=\"http://www.lafkon.net/tc/\" title=\"一个关于可信计算的很好的视频\">更准确地</a>说是\"奸诈的计算(Treacherous Computing)\")就是一台只能被运行“可信”的软件的计算机。其目的是为了防止滋扰(如病毒和恶意软件)和版权侵犯(拷贝有版权的软件)。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:92
msgid "Trusted Computing is control over the computer"
msgstr "可信计算控制着我们的计算机！"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:95
msgid ""
"The critical thing about Trusted Computing is that <strong>you cannot "
"decide</strong> what is trustworthy and what is not. For example, your "
"computer might refuse to run programs that are not certified by the software"
" company &ndash;programs that could enable you to take documents out of the "
"office, or play your neighbour's DVD, or send your essay to someone not "
"using the same program."
msgstr "可信计算带来的最严重的问题是，<strong>您不能决定</strong>什么是可信的而什么不是。您的计算机可能会拒绝运行没有受到软件厂商认证的程序——这可能是一个让您把文档带出办公室，或是播放您邻居的DVD，或者让您给并不使用同一软件的人发送信息的软件。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:96
msgid ""
"A whole range of possibilities opens up for companies that benefit from "
"restricting your computing (such as proprietary software and recording "
"companies). It is suddenly possible to rent DVDs that only play two times, "
"or music you can only listen to during September, or information you can "
"read but can't save or copy. All of a sudden, Trusted Computing and DRM "
"enable <strong>remote control</strong> over content."
msgstr "这所有的可能性使得公司（比如专有软件和音像公司）能够限制您的计算机。租到一个只能播放两次的DVD，购买到只能在九月听的音乐，或者只能阅读而不能保存的信息成为了现实。就在突然之间，信任计算和DRM开启了通过内容<strong>远程控制</strong>的时代。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:97
msgid ""
"Trusted Computing, in effect, enables the publisher to write their own "
"copyright law."
msgstr "可信计算事实上允许了发行商编写自己的版权法律。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:100
msgid "The wider impact"
msgstr "更广的影响"

#. translators: This is the quote by Rosemary Bechler in the middle of the
#. article.
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:105
msgid ""
"Many cultural products are now emerging &quot;triple protected&quot;, not "
"only by copyright and code, but also by contracts or licenses for which "
"users waive all remaining rights."
msgstr "文化产品现在集成了“三重保护”，不止被版权和法规保护，还有许多的合同和许可证使得用户放弃所剩无几的权利。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:106
msgid ""
"Increasingly, copyright is replaced with click-through end-user licenses for"
" digital content, using contract law to establish the absolute property "
"rights that copyright laws were originally intended to deny to publishers."
msgstr "越来越多的版权被最终用户点击通过的数字内容许可证取代，发行商使用合同法建立了原来版权法拒绝给予的绝对财产权利。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:110
msgid ""
"Computing is not just about calculations anymore. We use software to "
"communicate: to share information, ideas and culture. Software is in our "
"phones, cars, media players, TVs, and gets to govern just about every new "
"device around us."
msgstr "计算再也不只是数字计算了。我们使用软件来交流：分享信息、想法和文化。软件在电话、汽车、多媒体播放器和电视中随处可见，并管理着我们身边的几乎每一个崭新的设备。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:117
msgid ""
"<strong>Software is increasingly used to enforce rules</strong>. Rules that "
"may or may not be the law. Rules that may or may not be fair. If the "
"software is not free there will be no space for the user to influence these "
"rules."
msgstr "<strong>软件逐渐被用于强制实行规则</strong>。规则可以、也可以不是法律，可以、也可以不公平。如果一个软件不自由，那么用户就永远也没有改变这些规则的余地。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:119
msgid ""
"Trusted Computing and DRM pave the way for a society in which culture and "
"information are not simply turned into products (they are right now, and "
"that is fine), but into <em>consumable</em> products."
msgstr "想想未来，文化和信息不再仅仅是商品(它们现在是，这很好)，而成为了一种耗材。可信计算和DRM为这样的社会铺平了一条道路。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:121
msgid ""
"Code is power. Most of today's work documents are written and encoded with "
"secret algorithms in proprietary software. What will be of tomorrow's books,"
" photos, films, essays, animations, music, news? Proprietary programs such "
"as Windows have no transparency. A free culture and a free society cannot "
"grow from such software."
msgstr "代码就是力量。许多今天的工作文档是在专有软件中完成的，它们被写于、编码于秘密的算法中。明天的书籍、摄影作品、电影、随笔、动画、音乐甚至新闻会有什么？像Windows这样的专有软件没有任何透明，一个自由的文明和自由的社会不会产生出如此的作品。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:123
#, php-format
msgid "May we suggest you <a href=\"%s\">switch to Linux</a>?"
msgstr "我们可以建议您<a href=\"%s\">拥抱 Linux </a>吗？"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:128
msgid ""
"Note that DRM is often referred to as \"Digital Rights Management\", "
"although it has little to do with rights &ndash; \"Digital Restrictions "
"Management\" is a more accurate name."
msgstr "注意：DRM是“数字版权管理(Digital Rights Management)”的简称。尽管它确实有做一些关于版权的事情，不过“数字限制管理(Digital Restrictions Management)是一个更恰切的名称。"

#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:138
msgid ""
"What is the Trusted Computing world like? This is a short story by Richard "
"Stallman that describes how this can affect any of us."
msgstr "您没有完全读过您的许可证吗？让我们来帮你完成这项工作吧。"

#. translators: Unless you know of a very good resource about DRM, please
#. point to the Wikipedia article about DRM in your language, if it exists
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:142
msgid "http://www.timj.co.uk/computing/politics-policy/drm/fallacy/"
msgstr "http://www.timj.co.uk/computing/politics-policy/drm/fallacy/"

#. translators: Title of external link
#: pages/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:144
msgid "The fallacy of DRM"
msgstr "DRM 谬论"

